(Ooonana OS v1 field guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What it is) Tj
T*
(Ooonana OS is a scratch-built Linux project with its own rootfs, boot flow, installer) Tj
T*
(experiments, WSL export, and custom ooonana package manager.) Tj
T*
(Debian or Ubuntu are host build tools only. Alpine APKs are imported into Ooonana .pkg) Tj
T*
(repos; the target OS installs Ooonana packages, not live Alpine APKs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Editions) Tj
T*
(minimal: BusyBox-style rootfs, kernel, GRUB disk, installer ISO, WSL rootfs, command) Tj
T*
(line AI.) Tj
T*
(full-i3: minimal plus i3, Xorg package set, wallpaper, logo assets, GUI installer) Tj
T*
(wizard, AI desktop app, full WSL rootfs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Package install) Tj
T*
(ooonana update) Tj
T*
(ooonana search nano) Tj
T*
(ooonana show nano) Tj
T*
(ooonana get nano --dry-run) Tj
T*
(ooonana get nano) Tj
T*
(ooonana files nano) Tj
T*
(ooonana verify nano) Tj
T*
(ooonana upgrade) Tj
T*
(ooonana remove nano) Tj
T*
(ooonana purge nano) Tj
T*
(ooonana fix nano --reinstall) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Cloud repo) Tj
T*
(Default cloud path is GitHub Releases:) Tj
T*
(ooonana-package-repo.tar.gz) Tj
T*
(https://github.com/Ooonana/Ooonana-OS/releases/download/packages-latest/ooonana-) Tj
T*
(package-repo.tar.gz) Tj
T*
(A repo tarball contains index.tsv, SHA256SUMS, *.pkg files, and archives/. ooonana) Tj
T*
(update extracts it into /var/cache/ooonana/repos/NAME.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Installer) Tj
T*
(Full-i3 live ISO boots i3 by default. The installer wizard has disk picker,) Tj
T*
(user/password, hostname, theme picker, package repo picker, progress log, failure) Tj
T*
(shell, and reboot prompt.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(First boot) Tj
T*
(ooonana setup --first-boot --gui can create user, set password, write network config,) Tj
T*
(choose theme, add cloud repo, and mark setup complete.) Tj
T*
ET
